  <description><![CDATA[<p>Stay in the modern, Scandi style Levi Black Apartments on your winter holiday to Lapland. The local ski bus (payable locally) stop is just across the road, providing easy access to the South Point ski slopes and the resort centre. </p>
<h2>Perfect for families</h2>
<p>These apartments have a warm and welcoming atmosphere so they'll comfortably accommodate you and your family. Each apartment is spread out across two floors so there will be plenty of room for everyone as well as communal areas for quality time. Make the most of your time away together - curl up on the sofa or relax together in on of the outdoor whirlpools. After days out in the freezing arctic temperatures, revive your muscles in your private sauna - there's one in each apartment! </p>
<h2>Food and drink </h2>
<p>With the supermarket across the road, these apartments are geared up for self catering. The fully equipped kitchen means you'll be able to cook some tasty meals to enjoy around the table with the family and friends. There are plenty of restaurants in town to check out too, which can be reached using the ski bus during the day or you can book a private taxi (payable locally) in the evening. If you're looking to fully relax after days spent exploring the wilderness on a snowmobile excursion, husky safari or reindeer sleigh ride, why not upgrade to half board? The Levi Black Apartments offer a meal delivery service, so that you can enjoy breakfasts and dinner from the comfort of your own apartment. </p>]]></description>
